-\subsection{Advanced Process Metrics}
-\label{sec:advanced-metrics}
-
-Beyond aggregate scores, we analyze the internal dynamics of team coordination (Table~\ref{tab:advanced_metrics}).
-\textbf{Verification Accuracy} is only 30.5\% across 3{,}651 verifier judgments: verifiers are wrong nearly 70\% of the time, with a false-negative rate of 3.9\%.
-This quantifies the mechanism behind the negative verification value reported in Section~\ref{sec:components}: verifiers reject valid solutions far more often than they catch genuine failures.
-\textbf{Recovery Rate} is 96\% (48/50 tasks): executors almost always recover from suboptimal planning, indicating that team robustness derives primarily from the executor's ability to adapt rather than from planning accuracy.
-\textbf{Archetype-conditional TNI} confirms that task structure matters: adversarial tasks show the highest average TNI (0.93), consistent with the intuition that specification traps create maximal information asymmetry and thus maximal team value.
-Discovery tasks (0.37) and open-ended tasks (0.34) show moderate benefit, while synthesis tasks (0.42) benefit when the planner successfully distills cross-document evidence.
-
