-\subsection{Contamination Resistance Validation}
-\label{sec:contamination}
-
-To validate that parameterized generators produce genuinely distinct instances, we compare development seeds (0--2) against held-out seeds (5--7) across 50 tasks (Table~\ref{tab:contamination}).
-Of the 50 tasks evaluated, 32 (64\%) produce workspace instances where all held-out files differ from their development counterparts.
-The mean Jaccard similarity between seed~0 and seed~5 workspaces is $0.715 \pm 0.231$: generators preserve structural complexity while varying surface parameters (variable names, configuration values, bug locations), ensuring that memorization of specific seed instances does not transfer to unseen seeds.
-Oracle scores on held-out seeds show consistent cross-seed ICC with development seeds, confirming that task difficulty is stable across generator instances rather than an artifact of particular parameter values.
